    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/5–2446</note>
                <head>No. 398<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Briefing Book Paper</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d398fn1">Annex 13 to the attachment to <ref target="#d177"
                            >document No. 177</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d398fn2">For other
                            extracts from this paper, see <ref target="#d259">documents Nos.
                                259</ref> and <ref target="#d509">509</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">European Territorial Settlements</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">i. germany</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The United States Government is opposed to the separation from Germany of the
                        Ruhr<note n="3" xml:id="d398fn3">For a map of the Ruhr, see <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_926">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                            facing p. 926</ref>.</note> or the left bank of the Rhine either by
                    internationalization or by other means. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-29">June 29,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
